==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fundamentalism
<hw>fundamentalism</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A system of
beliefs based on the interpretation of every word in the Bible, both old
and new testaments, as literal truth. It is primarily held by a branch
of American Protestants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The beliefs or practices based on a rigid adherence
to some traditional doctrine; extreme conservatism; <as>as, Moslem
<ex>fundamentalism</ex>; the political <ex>fundamentalism</ex> of the
Christian right</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fundamentalistic</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>fundamentalist</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>
